#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:1
msgid "v0.3.0 — Trade History Viewer: Design Document"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:3
msgid ""
"**Status**: Draft, revision 5 (locale-split YAML + UI i18n switcher; W-1 "
"spike result) **Target ship**: 2-3 weeks of part-time dev **Languages in "
"this doc**: English (primary, OSS-facing). Japanese sibling: [`v0.3"
"-trade-history-design.ja.md`](./v0.3-trade-history-design.ja.md) **Last "
"updated**: 2026-04-19"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:8
msgid "1. Overview / 概要"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:10
msgid ""
"`anno-save-analyzer` v0.3.0 ships a **Trade History Viewer** — a CLI + "
"Textual TUI for inspecting trade activity recorded inside Anno save files"
" (`.a7s`, `.a8s`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:12
msgid ""
"Unlike Anno 1800, **Anno 117: Pax Romana ships without a built-in trade-"
"history UI** (as of patch 1.4 / 2026-04). Ubisoft's *Thorlof* has "
"acknowledged the gap as \"on the list\" but no ETA exists. This tool "
"fills that gap in pure Python, on top of the v0.1/v0.2 RDA + FileDB "
"parsers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:14
msgid "**Design pillars** (in priority order):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:16
msgid ""
"**Dogfooding first**: the primary user is the maintainer (書記長), who "
"actively plays Anno 117 and wants per-good and per-route trade insights "
"to inform supply-chain decisions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:17
msgid ""
"**Cross-title abstraction**: the data model is title-agnostic so that "
"future Anno releases (or even reimaginings) plug in via a thin "
"interpreter layer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:18
msgid ""
"**Bounded scope**: ships in 2-3 weeks of part-time work. Anything that "
"does not directly serve dogfooding is deferred."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:19
msgid ""
"**Streaming-friendly**: handles 500MB+ inner FileDB binaries via the "
"existing `parser.filedb.iter_dom` streaming iterator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:21
msgid ""
"This document **does not contain implementation code**. It freezes the "
"contract that v0.3 will be built against."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:23
msgid "2. User Stories / ユーザーストーリー"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:25
msgid "2.1 書記長 (Primary — dogfooding operator)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:27
msgid ""
"書記長 plays Anno 117 with a deliberate \"5-good strategy\" to keep "
"cognitive load down. Decisions about which routes to keep, which trade "
"partners to favour, and which goods to over-produce currently rely on "
"guesswork because the in-game UI gives no historical view."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:30
msgid ""
"US-1. **As 書記長**, I want to load my latest `.a8s` save and see which "
"goods were traded the most over the last in-game period, so I can verify "
"my 5-good strategy is being respected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:31
msgid ""
"US-2. **As 書記長**, I want to see per-route balance (cost vs. revenue per "
"active route) so I can kill or rewire routes that bleed gold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:32
msgid ""
"US-3. **As 書記長**, I want to keep snapshots of my saves over time and "
"compare them, so I can reconstruct trade history even if Anno 117 doesn't"
" record it natively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:33
msgid ""
"US-4. **As 書記長**, I want everything to run from a terminal — no Electron,"
" no browser — because my daily flow is WSL2 + tmux + Vim."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:35
msgid "2.2 Anno 117 community (Secondary — English-speaking)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:37
msgid ""
"US-5. **As an Anno 117 player**, I want a CLI command that exports trade "
"history to JSON so I can analyse it in my own spreadsheet/notebook tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:38
msgid ""
"US-6. **As an Anno 117 modder**, I want a documented data model so I can "
"write extensions (e.g. enrich GUIDs with mod-specific item names)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:40
msgid "2.3 Anno 1800 legacy users (Tertiary)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/design/v0.3-trade-history-design.md:42
msgid ""
"US-7. **As an Anno 1800 player**, I want the same viewer to work on "
"`.a7s` saves with minimal config (different YAML mapping is acceptable)."
msgstr ""

